<item>
            <title>[SPARK-19334] Fix the code injection vulnerability related to Generator functions.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-19334</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15165&quot; title=&quot;Codegen can break because toCommentSafeString is not actually safe&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-15165&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-15165&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, codegen is in danger of arbitrary code injection. The root cause is how variable names are created by codegen.&lt;br/&gt;
In GenerateExec#codeGenAccessor, a variable name is created like as follows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;val value = ctx.freshName(name)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The variable `value` is named based on the value of the variable `name` and the value of `name` is from schema given by user so an attacker can attack with queries like as follows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;SELECT inline(array(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;cast&lt;/span&gt;(struct(1) AS struct&amp;lt;`=&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;() { {f();} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; void f() {&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RuntimeException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;This exception is injected.&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; x;}.x`:&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;)))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the example above, a RuntimeException is thrown but attacker can replace it with arbitrary code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
